<h2>Workflow</h2>
<p>
    Multi-step process orchestration without URL changes &mdash; wizard-like flows with per-step validation,
    linear/branching progression, and state persistence. The non-route complement to
    <a href="/blocks/router/">Router</a>'s URL-based step navigation.
</p>
<p>
    Workflow reuses <a href="/blocks/view/">ViewEngine</a>'s exclusive group pattern for step visibility
    and <code>&lt;fieldset&gt;</code> for semantic grouping. Steps are always in the DOM (like
    <a href="/blocks/tabs/">Tabs</a> panels), preserving form state across forward/back navigation.
</p>

<h3>Architecture: Router vs Workflow</h3>
<p>
    <a href="/blocks/router/">Router</a> handles URL-based multi-step flows (checkout with bookmarkable steps,
    onboarding wizards with shareable links). Workflow handles <strong>state-based</strong> flows where
    URL changes are unnecessary or undesirable: modal wizards, in-page forms, short processes.
</p>
<table>
    <thead>
        <tr><th></th><th>Router (URL-based)</th><th>Workflow (State-based)</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>Step identity</strong></td>
            <td>URL path (<code>/checkout/payment</code>)</td>
            <td>Attribute value (<code>workflow-step="payment"</code>)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>Browser back/forward</strong></td>
            <td>Native (Navigation API)</td>
            <td>Optional (History API pushState or none)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>Bookmarkable</strong></td>
            <td>Yes</td>
            <td>No (or via query params)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>Step content</strong></td>
            <td>Stamped on demand from <code>&lt;template&gt;</code></td>
            <td>Always in DOM, hidden when inactive</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>State on refresh</strong></td>
            <td>Preserved (URL encodes step)</td>
            <td>Lost unless <code>withAutoSave</code> persists to storage</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>Use case</strong></td>
            <td>Multi-page checkout, onboarding</td>
            <td>Modal wizards, in-page forms, settings flows</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<h3>Web Standards Alignment</h3>
<table>
    <tr><th>Standard</th><th>Status</th><th>How We Adopt It</th></tr>
    <tr>
        <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Guides/Constraint_validation">Constraint Validation API</a></td>
        <td>Baseline</td>
        <td><code>withGateValidation</code> calls <code>checkValidity()</code> on the active step's <code>&lt;fieldset&gt;</code> before allowing advancement; hidden steps are automatically skipped</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/fieldset">&lt;fieldset&gt;</a></td>
        <td>Standard</td>
        <td>Each step wraps content in <code>&lt;fieldset&gt;</code>; inactive steps get <code>disabled</code> attribute to prevent interaction and exclude from validation</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Attributes/aria-current">aria-current</a></td>
        <td>Standard</td>
        <td>Step indicator uses <code>&lt;ol&gt;</code> with <code>aria-current="step"</code> on the active <code>&lt;li&gt;</code></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Invoker_Commands_API">Invoker Commands API</a></td>
        <td>Baseline 2026</td>
        <td>Next/Previous buttons use <code>commandfor</code> targeting the workflow element with <code>command="--workflow-next"</code> / <code>command="--workflow-prev"</code></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Guides/Scroll_snap">CSS Scroll Snap</a></td>
        <td>Baseline</td>
        <td>Optional: <code>scroll-snap-type: x mandatory</code> for horizontal step transitions; <code>scrollsnapchange</code> event for JS hooks</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/dialog">&lt;dialog&gt;</a></td>
        <td>Baseline</td>
        <td>When workflow is inside a <code>&lt;dialog&gt;</code>, focus management delegates to the browser's native dialog focusing steps</td>
    </tr>
</table>

